    <para>Warning is an admonition, usually set off from main text.</para>
    <para>Warning is meant to imply reader of the possibility of harm. For example: <sgmltag>caution</sgmltag> could imply harm to equipment while <sgmltag>warning</sgmltag> could imply harm to a person.</para>
    <para>Differences between admonitions are not defined in DocBook.</para>
    <para>Warning requires <sgmltag>para</sgmltag> or other elements for displaying any text.</para>
    <note>
        <title>Source</title>
        <para>DocBook: The Definitive Guide : <ulink url="http://www.docbook.org/tdg/en/html/warning.html" /></para>
    </note>
    <section>
        <title>warning in db2xhtml Library</title>
        <para>Style at <filename>~css/block.css</filename> element div.e_warning {}</para>
        <para>Processing at <filename>~xsl/elements/block/warning.xsl</filename></para>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>Example of warning</title>
        <para>Example how db2xhtml Library presents <sgmltag>warning</sgmltag>.</para>
        <para>Basic use of warning with title</para>
        <warning>
            <title>Warning title</title>
            <para>This is a warning example.</para>
        </warning>
        <para>XML lines</para>
        <programlisting><![CDATA[<warning>
<title>Warning title</title>
<para>This is a warning example</para>
</warning>]]></programlisting>
        <para>Also, warning can have many different elements inside</para>
        <para>Here's example with <sgmltag>itemizedlist</sgmltag></para>
        <warning>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem><para>First item</para></listitem>
                <listitem><para>Second item</para></listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </warning>
        <para>And XML lines</para>
        <programlisting><![CDATA[<warning>
    <itemizedlist>
        <listitem><para>First item</para></listitem>
        <listitem><para>Second item</para></listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
</warning>]]></programlisting>
    </section>
